\b Smart Irrigation System – Comprehensive Documentation (API + Remote Usage + System Overview)\b0\par
\par
\b 1) Overview\b0\par
Purpose: Provide real-time irrigation control, soil health analytics, and crop recommendations via a Flask web service integrated with an Arduino-based sensor/pump system.\par
Stack: Flask (Python), Pandas/NumPy/Plotly, scikit-learn (optional), HTML/CSS/JS, Arduino over serial.\par
Key files:\par
- water_harvest_dashboard.py (Flask server, serial IO, decisions, APIs)\par
- soil_health_monitor.py (historical soil analytics, charts, farmer summary)\par
- crop_recommendation.py (synthetic dataset, model training, recommendations)\par
- templates/*.html (UI pages)\par
- models/* (datasets, model pickles, metadata)\par
\par
\b 2) Environments and Base URLs\b0\par
- Local (same PC): http://127.0.0.1:5000\par
- Remote (public, tunnel): e.g., https://earlene-unrecognizable-vaughn.ngrok-free.dev\par
\par
When calling from another machine or a mobile app, replace the local base URL with your public tunnel domain.\par
\par
\b 3) HTML Pages (Full UI)\b0\par
- GET / – Main dashboard (live telemetry, decisions, alerts, log stats, controls)\par
- GET /soil-health – Soil Health Analytics (charts + farmer-friendly summary)\par
- GET /crop-recommend – Crop Recommendations (responsive on phones)\par
\par
